A man has been arrested on suspicion of sexually assaulting a child near a Devon park, police say.
Devon and Cornwall Police said officers were called to reports of a man with a "clown-type mask" scaring children near Newcombes Play Park in Crediton at about 12:00 BST. 
Officers said they arrested a man in his 40s on suspicion of sexually assaulting a child.
He remains in police custody while inquiries continue.
Insp Ollie Heaton said police were not looking for anyone else.
"I want to reassure the public that we are painstakingly seeking all the evidence in order to deal robustly and thoroughly with the report," he said.
The force encouraged potential witnesses to get in touch with them.
